1
00:00:07,400 --> 00:00:10,140
A standard six-string guitar has 21 frets.

2
00:00:10,670 --> 00:00:13,810
Each fret represents
a half-step up in pitch.

3
00:00:22,550 --> 00:00:24,890
He once told me

4
00:00:24,890 --> 00:00:26,190
that the first fret

5
00:00:26,190 --> 00:00:27,720
isn't the highest note

6
00:00:27,890 --> 00:00:29,390
or the brightest one,

7
00:00:29,720 --> 00:00:32,320
but it feels like
the beginning of everything.

8
00:00:35,260 --> 00:00:37,070
You've failed so many times.

9
00:00:37,790 --> 00:00:39,650
Are you still going to keep going?

10
00:00:41,140 --> 00:00:42,240
The first fret

11
00:00:42,440 --> 00:00:43,970
has no flashy technique,

12
00:00:44,260 --> 00:00:45,490
no speed—

13
00:00:45,770 --> 00:00:46,880
only the possibility

14
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:49,180
that it's not too late to turn back.

15
00:00:50,410 --> 00:00:51,710
And that possibility

16
00:00:51,780 --> 00:00:53,420
is the truest,

17
00:00:53,780 --> 00:00:56,240
most heart-stirring starting point for us.

18
00:01:43,150 --> 00:01:48,460
[Smile After Tears]

19
00:01:48,680 --> 00:01:51,880
[First Fret: The Heart-Flutter
of a First Touch]

20
00:01:55,280 --> 00:01:59,950
He!

21
00:02:14,030 --> 00:02:16,500
This was my first time meeting He.

22
00:02:20,970 --> 00:02:22,829
To explain how all this happened,

23
00:02:23,320 --> 00:02:25,590
I have to start with my morning.

24
00:02:47,010 --> 00:02:47,590
[Convenience Store – Night Shift]

25
00:02:47,600 --> 00:02:47,890
[Wednesday, September 6, 2023]

26
00:02:47,910 --> 00:02:48,390
[New Schedule Added:
Convenience Store – Night Shift]

27
00:02:49,840 --> 00:02:50,050
[New Schedule Added:
Convenience Store – Night Shift]

28
00:02:50,050 --> 00:02:51,780
[Korean Fried Chicken Shop – Night Shift]

29
00:02:51,910 --> 00:02:52,579
[Convenience Store – Night Shift]

30
00:03:16,220 --> 00:03:17,290
Morning, Grandma.

31
00:03:17,290 --> 00:03:18,160
Morning.

32
00:03:18,160 --> 00:03:19,230
Are you going to school?

33
00:03:19,230 --> 00:03:19,890
Yes.

34
00:03:22,700 --> 00:03:23,600
Let me help you.

35
00:03:23,770 --> 00:03:24,270
No need.

36
00:03:24,270 --> 00:03:25,170
I can do it myself.

37
00:03:25,170 --> 00:03:26,170
It's okay.

38
00:03:35,780 --> 00:03:38,210
I wonder if you've ever had this feeling—

39
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:41,440
doing the same things every single day,

40
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:51,600
stuck in the same routine day after day.

41
00:03:51,730 --> 00:03:53,260
It's ordinary,

42
00:03:53,550 --> 00:03:54,880
but simple.

43
00:04:03,850 --> 00:04:10,640
[Zhang Junjia]

44
00:04:12,840 --> 00:04:13,770
Hello, everyone.

45
00:04:13,770 --> 00:04:15,070
I'm Junjia.

46
00:04:15,250 --> 00:04:16,579
What I'm best at is

47
00:04:16,579 --> 00:04:18,120
smiling even after falling down,

48
00:04:18,120 --> 00:04:19,790
and still daring to sing
even when I'm off-key.

49
00:04:19,790 --> 00:04:20,820
Because I believe

50
00:04:20,820 --> 00:04:22,480
that as long as I keep smiling,

51
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:24,590
the people around me will be happy too.

52
00:04:24,590 --> 00:04:25,550
Thank you.

53
00:04:29,580 --> 00:04:30,550
Just sit there.

54
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:31,570
Next time,

55
00:04:31,570 --> 00:04:32,960
remember to wear the school uniform.

56
00:04:32,960 --> 00:04:34,159
Okay, thank you.

57
00:04:34,190 --> 00:04:34,850
Have a seat.

58
00:04:38,380 --> 00:04:41,620
Okay, please turn to page 10.

59
00:04:52,450 --> 00:04:53,720
So you moved

60
00:04:53,720 --> 00:04:55,590
because of

61
00:04:55,920 --> 00:04:57,050
your family's work?

62
00:04:57,159 --> 00:04:57,930
Yes.

63
00:04:57,930 --> 00:05:00,130
Luckily I was only in first year before,

64
00:05:00,130 --> 00:05:03,150
otherwise I probably
would've had a much harder time leaving.

65
00:05:03,150 --> 00:05:04,900
So this time you won't be

66
00:05:04,900 --> 00:05:06,580
transferring schools again, right?

67
00:05:06,580 --> 00:05:07,560
No.

68
00:05:07,940 --> 00:05:10,080
My aunt has a stable job this time,

69
00:05:10,170 --> 00:05:11,570
and she even brought in
some former coworkers

70
00:05:11,570 --> 00:05:13,040
to help out.

71
00:05:13,370 --> 00:05:15,230
I probably won't be moving again.

72
00:05:19,190 --> 00:05:19,820
By the way,

73
00:05:20,280 --> 00:05:21,220
you're lucky.

74
00:05:21,740 --> 00:05:23,850
You transferred in just in time
for the club fair.

75
00:05:23,850 --> 00:05:24,990
A lot of clubs will be putting on
performances

76
00:05:24,990 --> 00:05:26,000
this afternoon.

77
00:05:26,350 --> 00:05:27,320
Really?

78
00:05:28,100 --> 00:05:29,050
Excuse me.

79
00:05:29,080 --> 00:05:30,740
Come join the board game club!

80
00:05:31,290 --> 00:05:32,690
He is the best!

81
00:05:32,720 --> 00:05:34,920
Are club fairs this intense every year?

82
00:05:35,100 --> 00:05:36,040
Almost.

83
00:05:36,600 --> 00:05:37,130
How is it?

84
00:05:37,170 --> 00:05:39,270
Seen any clubs you like yet?

85
00:05:39,630 --> 00:05:40,690
There are too many.

86
00:05:40,770 --> 00:05:42,300
I still need to look around.

87
00:05:42,540 --> 00:05:45,140
We're classmates
and already know each other,

88
00:05:46,870 --> 00:05:48,180
so how about joining the basketball team?

89
00:05:48,180 --> 00:05:49,070
[Basketball Team]

90
00:05:49,140 --> 00:05:50,940
We could look out for each other.

91
00:05:51,450 --> 00:05:53,580
But I'm really not good at basketball.

92
00:05:54,900 --> 00:05:55,950
I can teach you.

93
00:05:56,250 --> 00:05:57,480
As long as you're willing to play,

94
00:05:57,480 --> 00:05:58,740
anything's possible.

95
00:06:00,440 --> 00:06:02,060
I can teach you how to shoot.

96
00:06:07,160 --> 00:06:08,400
It looks pretty lively over there.

97
00:06:08,400 --> 00:06:09,800
I'm gonna go check it out.

98
00:06:10,250 --> 00:06:10,880
Go ahead.

99
00:06:11,900 --> 00:06:12,570
So cute!

100
00:06:12,570 --> 00:06:13,500
So cute!

101
00:06:14,140 --> 00:06:18,210
He!

102
00:06:18,240 --> 00:06:23,570
[He]

103
00:06:21,300 --> 00:06:22,770
He!

104
00:06:58,810 --> 00:06:59,680
Be careful.

105
00:07:00,870 --> 00:07:02,080
Thank you.

106
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:11,910
He!

107
00:07:14,010 --> 00:07:17,380
He!

108
00:07:17,450 --> 00:07:21,170
He!

109
00:07:28,710 --> 00:07:33,140
♪ 1440 minutes before our date ♪

110
00:07:33,280 --> 00:07:35,830
♪ Baby, baby, promise me ♪

111
00:07:36,010 --> 00:07:39,270
♪ Don't shatter my dreams ♪

112
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:43,770
♪ 1440 minutes before our date ♪

113
00:07:44,020 --> 00:07:46,620
♪ What should I do ♪

114
00:07:46,740 --> 00:07:49,930
♪ To turn you into my miracle ♪

115
00:07:50,020 --> 00:07:52,440
♪ Just one touch from your fingertips ♪

116
00:07:52,590 --> 00:07:55,110
♪ Sends my heartbeat racing ♪

117
00:07:55,260 --> 00:07:58,490
♪ Missing you needs no second guessing ♪

118
00:07:58,610 --> 00:08:01,640
♪ Your are my miracle ♪

119
00:08:01,740 --> 00:08:06,530
♪ Miracle Miracle ♪

120
00:08:06,730 --> 00:08:09,290
♪ My miracle ♪

121
00:08:07,350 --> 00:08:09,550
This was our first meeting.

122
00:08:09,980 --> 00:08:11,950
It was obviously just an accident,

123
00:08:12,190 --> 00:08:14,460
but my heart started racing so fast.

124
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:19,850
It felt like someone

125
00:08:20,230 --> 00:08:22,630
had suddenly switched on
a light inside me,

126
00:08:22,700 --> 00:08:25,830
so bright that I couldn't see anything
clearly anymore.

127
00:08:32,010 --> 00:08:33,700
[Hi-Life]

128
00:08:32,730 --> 00:08:34,370
I've never seen him before.

129
00:08:35,260 --> 00:08:36,429
How did this happen?

130
00:08:38,850 --> 00:08:39,650
Wei,

131
00:08:39,809 --> 00:08:42,809
do you think I've caught
some kind of serious illness?

132
00:08:43,350 --> 00:08:44,020
Well,

133
00:08:44,520 --> 00:08:45,520
lovesickness.

134
00:08:46,990 --> 00:08:48,020
Love?

135
00:08:49,230 --> 00:08:50,340
No way.

136
00:08:50,360 --> 00:08:52,980
It's only my first day
after transferring schools here.

137
00:08:52,980 --> 00:08:55,430
Love at first sight is totally possible.

138
00:08:58,790 --> 00:09:00,130
According to research,

139
00:09:00,150 --> 00:09:02,720
within 0.1 of a second
of seeing a stranger,

140
00:09:02,910 --> 00:09:06,710
our brains already begin
judging their safety and attractiveness.

141
00:09:07,310 --> 00:09:08,860
So, Zhang Junjia,

142
00:09:08,940 --> 00:09:10,070
congratulations on

143
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:12,130
falling in love for the first time.

144
00:09:15,890 --> 00:09:16,950
Welcome.

145
00:09:52,820 --> 00:09:54,120
Just one touch of your fingertips

146
00:09:54,120 --> 00:09:56,390
and my whole heartbeat short-circuits.

147
00:10:26,440 --> 00:10:28,900
Love at first sight is totally possible.

148
00:10:31,280 --> 00:10:32,410
Congratulations on

149
00:10:32,500 --> 00:10:34,430
falling in love for the first time.

150
00:10:41,040 --> 00:10:41,670
Junior,

151
00:10:41,670 --> 00:10:43,730
do you want to join the Hot Music Club?

152
00:10:45,770 --> 00:10:46,910
Hello.

153
00:10:46,930 --> 00:10:47,980
Junior, you're here.

154
00:10:47,980 --> 00:10:48,480
Hurry up.

155
00:10:48,480 --> 00:10:49,200
Come in.

156
00:10:49,260 --> 00:10:50,310
Come, sit here.

157
00:11:11,550 --> 00:11:12,650
So handsome.

158
00:11:14,200 --> 00:11:14,770
Who?

159
00:11:15,540 --> 00:11:16,260
Me?

160
00:11:16,640 --> 00:11:17,770
Junior,

161
00:11:17,790 --> 00:11:18,890
come on…

162
00:11:19,140 --> 00:11:20,410
Everyone knows I'm handsome.

163
00:11:20,410 --> 00:11:21,580
By the way, senior,

164
00:11:21,580 --> 00:11:23,380
I want to join the Hot Music Club.

165
00:11:23,580 --> 00:11:24,810
Nice,

166
00:11:24,810 --> 00:11:27,010
junior. Good taste.

167
00:11:28,080 --> 00:11:29,420
But...

168
00:11:29,580 --> 00:11:31,450
Why aren't you in our school uniform?

169
00:11:31,450 --> 00:11:32,520
I just transferred here.

170
00:11:32,520 --> 00:11:34,250
I haven't had time to buy it yet.

171
00:11:34,620 --> 00:11:35,480
I see.

172
00:11:35,620 --> 00:11:37,080
You're very welcome here.

173
00:11:37,090 --> 00:11:37,730
Come.

174
00:11:45,130 --> 00:11:46,670
Everyone,

175
00:11:47,270 --> 00:11:50,000
we're really glad you're
interested in joining,

176
00:11:50,070 --> 00:11:50,840
so

177
00:11:50,840 --> 00:11:52,740
this time we'll be selecting members

178
00:11:52,740 --> 00:11:54,470
based on ability and interest.

179
00:11:54,580 --> 00:11:56,190
It's a necessary step—

180
00:11:56,380 --> 00:11:58,970
we want to see where everyone stands.

181
00:11:59,110 --> 00:11:59,880
So,

182
00:12:00,060 --> 00:12:01,720
I'll be sending you a demo track.

183
00:12:01,720 --> 00:12:03,020
After you listen to it,

184
00:12:03,020 --> 00:12:04,890
feel free to create something of your own—
write lyrics,

185
00:12:04,890 --> 00:12:06,720
or if you've got ideas,

186
00:12:06,820 --> 00:12:08,890
you can add melodies too.

187
00:12:09,220 --> 00:12:10,830
Please hand it in next week.

188
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:12,860
Any questions about

189
00:12:12,860 --> 00:12:13,780
Hot Music Club?

190
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:20,460
Anything at all, just ask.

191
00:12:22,270 --> 00:12:23,730
Come on, junior. Go ahead.

192
00:12:24,570 --> 00:12:25,340
Well,

193
00:12:26,040 --> 00:12:27,740
at the expo,

194
00:12:27,740 --> 00:12:29,110
there's a line in your song

195
00:12:29,110 --> 00:12:30,310
I don't really get.

196
00:12:41,660 --> 00:12:43,170
I wrote both the lyrics and the music.

197
00:12:43,170 --> 00:12:44,300
What's the problem?

198
00:12:53,770 --> 00:12:55,440
It's not a big problem.

199
00:12:55,840 --> 00:12:57,250
It's just this line

200
00:12:57,670 --> 00:12:59,140
feels a bit off to me.

201
00:12:59,440 --> 00:13:01,210
Why does it say,
"Just one touch of your fingertips

202
00:13:01,210 --> 00:13:03,540
and my whole heartbeat short-circuits?"

203
00:13:07,410 --> 00:13:08,440
Well,

204
00:13:08,470 --> 00:13:10,770
-about this queastion...
-You all get out.

205
00:13:10,770 --> 00:13:11,300
He.

206
00:13:11,320 --> 00:13:11,860
Well…

207
00:13:11,890 --> 00:13:13,250
-He didn't know; he just came.
-I mean

208
00:13:13,250 --> 00:13:14,470
everyone out.

209
00:13:19,930 --> 00:13:21,030
Hey,

210
00:13:21,770 --> 00:13:23,360
I'll treat everyone to drinks.

211
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:24,360
Come on, let's go.

212
00:13:24,960 --> 00:13:25,830
Come on.

213
00:13:28,440 --> 00:13:29,970
What are you talking about?

214
00:13:41,470 --> 00:13:42,780
Why are you stepping back?

215
00:13:42,780 --> 00:13:43,510
Come closer.

216
00:13:45,190 --> 00:13:45,790
Me?

217
00:13:46,080 --> 00:13:47,540
Is there anyone else here?

218
00:13:48,860 --> 00:13:50,520
So you think my lyric

219
00:13:51,070 --> 00:13:51,860
is problematic?

220
00:13:51,860 --> 00:13:53,460
I don't mean to question you.

221
00:13:54,330 --> 00:13:55,360
I just think

222
00:13:56,230 --> 00:13:58,620
my heart wouldn't be short-circuited.

223
00:13:58,930 --> 00:13:59,830
Then what?

224
00:14:11,950 --> 00:14:12,580
What?

225
00:14:13,640 --> 00:14:14,810
“A heartbeat

226
00:14:15,170 --> 00:14:16,570
doesn't short-circuit.

227
00:14:19,020 --> 00:14:20,120
It should be…

228
00:14:20,720 --> 00:14:21,620
a flutter.

229
00:14:37,450 --> 00:14:39,110
Since you think you're better than me,

230
00:14:39,110 --> 00:14:39,880
you can

231
00:14:39,900 --> 00:14:41,630
write all the lyrics tomorrow.

232
00:14:41,990 --> 00:14:43,990
Otherwise, quit the Hot Music Club.

233
00:14:57,430 --> 00:15:00,400
[Dalang Korean medley –
fried chicken, drinks]

234
00:15:22,690 --> 00:15:24,620
Do you have something in your hand?

235
00:15:26,230 --> 00:15:27,360
Does that look nice?

236
00:15:28,640 --> 00:15:29,620
Our cute part-timer seems

237
00:15:29,620 --> 00:15:30,490
a bit off today.

238
00:15:31,210 --> 00:15:32,040
No.

239
00:15:32,280 --> 00:15:34,930
I was just thinking about
something at school.

240
00:15:34,950 --> 00:15:35,570
What is it?

241
00:15:35,600 --> 00:15:36,740
Tell us about it.

242
00:15:36,950 --> 00:15:38,050
Well,

243
00:15:39,750 --> 00:15:40,880
I'm curious—

244
00:15:40,900 --> 00:15:42,100
have you ever had your heart beat

245
00:15:42,100 --> 00:15:43,470
really fast like that?

246
00:15:53,540 --> 00:15:54,870
Yeah, it does beat fast.

247
00:16:02,480 --> 00:16:03,810
Really fast.

248
00:16:08,250 --> 00:16:09,600
Not like that…

249
00:16:10,150 --> 00:16:12,130
I mean, like when you're

250
00:16:12,570 --> 00:16:13,640
thinking about someone

251
00:16:13,640 --> 00:16:14,220
and then…

252
00:16:14,870 --> 00:16:15,450
Wait.

253
00:16:15,940 --> 00:16:17,370
Are you dating someone?

254
00:16:17,630 --> 00:16:19,000
Who do you like?

255
00:16:19,120 --> 00:16:20,120
Tell me.

256
00:16:20,170 --> 00:16:20,810
Who?

257
00:16:20,810 --> 00:16:21,840
Are you in a relationship?

258
00:16:21,840 --> 00:16:22,500
No.

259
00:16:22,530 --> 00:16:23,380
You're exaggerating.

260
00:16:23,380 --> 00:16:24,680
-Who do you like?
-No, I don't.

261
00:16:24,680 --> 00:16:25,680
Who do you like?

262
00:16:25,680 --> 00:16:26,540
There's no one.

263
00:16:26,690 --> 00:16:29,370
[Dalang (Korean skewers, fried chicken, drinks)]

264
00:16:45,030 --> 00:16:46,200
Poor thing.

265
00:16:46,220 --> 00:16:47,620
He's too arrogant.

266
00:16:48,070 --> 00:16:50,130
Let's see how long he can be arrogant.

267
00:17:14,520 --> 00:17:15,359
Auntie,

268
00:17:15,380 --> 00:17:16,680
did you just come back?

269
00:17:23,420 --> 00:17:24,220
I picked this up

270
00:17:24,220 --> 00:17:25,599
from the pharmacy.

271
00:17:25,930 --> 00:17:28,369
You're on the machine every day.

272
00:17:28,600 --> 00:17:30,230
Your shoulders must be really sore,

273
00:17:30,230 --> 00:17:31,220
so I got you this.

274
00:17:31,250 --> 00:17:32,050
Why haven't you bought

275
00:17:32,050 --> 00:17:33,580
the new school uniform yet?

276
00:17:34,900 --> 00:17:36,600
The school's already called.

277
00:17:39,350 --> 00:17:40,280
I forgot.

278
00:17:40,710 --> 00:17:42,660
I thought that after paying for
water, electricity, and rent,

279
00:17:42,660 --> 00:17:44,340
there'd still be enough left to buy it,

280
00:17:44,340 --> 00:17:45,010
so I…

281
00:18:19,410 --> 00:18:22,210
Why haven't you bought
the new school uniform yet?

282
00:18:23,300 --> 00:18:25,070
The school's already called.

283
00:18:37,880 --> 00:18:40,070
[Auntie]

284
00:18:38,170 --> 00:18:39,130
Thank you.

285
00:18:57,470 --> 00:18:58,890
Since you think better than me,

286
00:18:58,890 --> 00:18:59,670
you can

287
00:18:59,670 --> 00:19:01,400
write all the lyrics tomorrow.

288
00:19:01,760 --> 00:19:03,760
Otherwise, quit the Hot Music Club.

289
00:20:28,110 --> 00:20:28,770
Galu.

290
00:20:40,240 --> 00:20:42,700
You didn't take the wrong medicine,
did you?

291
00:20:51,780 --> 00:20:56,250
[Isn't that the transfer student
who talked back to Senior He?]

292
00:21:00,420 --> 00:21:01,130
Look.

293
00:21:01,160 --> 00:21:01,990
It's him.

294
00:21:02,010 --> 00:21:03,160
The one who questioned Senior He?

295
00:21:03,160 --> 00:21:04,760
Yes, that transfer student.

296
00:21:08,160 --> 00:21:08,900
Don't look.

297
00:21:09,260 --> 00:21:10,460
Don't listen either.

298
00:21:10,660 --> 00:21:11,530
Diaoqin.

299
00:21:14,770 --> 00:21:15,740
Ignore them.

300
00:21:16,340 --> 00:21:17,870
Nothing's going to happen.

301
00:21:20,100 --> 00:21:21,080
[Isn't that the transfer student
who talked back to Senior He?]

302
00:21:21,100 --> 00:21:24,840
[He's so rude to He.]

303
00:21:24,860 --> 00:21:25,720
[Poor thing, working part-time late at night.
No wonder he can't afford a new uniform.]

304
00:21:29,580 --> 00:21:31,390
They made me look so ugly.

305
00:21:31,720 --> 00:21:32,390
Look.

306
00:21:33,490 --> 00:21:34,290
Are you

307
00:21:34,540 --> 00:21:35,710
really okay?

308
00:21:37,020 --> 00:21:38,580
Others move their mouths as they like;

309
00:21:38,580 --> 00:21:39,620
I don't care about

310
00:21:39,640 --> 00:21:40,600
this trivial

311
00:21:41,880 --> 00:21:42,380
Okay.

312
00:21:42,400 --> 00:21:43,360
We're going to be late.

313
00:21:43,360 --> 00:21:44,130
Let's go.

314
00:21:47,060 --> 00:21:48,500
That's all for today.

315
00:21:48,530 --> 00:21:49,340
Class is over.

316
00:21:49,810 --> 00:21:51,250
Let's play basketball!

317
00:21:52,070 --> 00:21:53,510
Diaoqin, come practice.

318
00:22:01,140 --> 00:22:02,030
Zhang Junjia,

319
00:22:03,580 --> 00:22:04,250
come out.

320
00:22:19,060 --> 00:22:19,900
Sorry.

321
00:22:24,270 --> 00:22:26,500
We spoke ill of you on the internet first.

322
00:22:26,500 --> 00:22:27,200
Sorry.

323
00:22:32,400 --> 00:22:34,150
I told you to change the lyrics.

324
00:22:34,150 --> 00:22:34,880
No.

325
00:22:35,480 --> 00:22:36,250
It'll flow better...

326
00:22:36,250 --> 00:22:36,820
No.

327
00:22:36,820 --> 00:22:37,830
If you change them.

328
00:22:37,830 --> 00:22:38,250
No.

329
00:22:38,270 --> 00:22:38,970
Senior!

330
00:22:38,510 --> 00:22:40,040
[Monument of Cultural
Exchange and Encounter]

331
00:22:39,800 --> 00:22:40,520
Senior.

332
00:22:47,160 --> 00:22:47,860
Thank you.

333
00:22:51,720 --> 00:22:53,660
Why did you suddenly apologize to me?

334
00:22:53,660 --> 00:22:54,800
He

335
00:22:54,960 --> 00:22:56,560
asked us to apologize to you.

336
00:22:57,620 --> 00:22:58,780
We're really sorry.

337
00:23:05,010 --> 00:23:06,210
I didn't do anything.

338
00:23:06,600 --> 00:23:08,400
I just checked the IP like before

339
00:23:08,430 --> 00:23:10,360
and found it pretty easily anyway.

340
00:23:13,230 --> 00:23:14,800
The point is—

341
00:23:15,390 --> 00:23:17,120
there aren't many people

342
00:23:17,120 --> 00:23:18,320
he actually praises.

343
00:23:20,430 --> 00:23:21,700
I've read your lyrics.

344
00:23:22,070 --> 00:23:23,270
They're pretty good.

345
00:23:30,380 --> 00:23:31,440
Thank you, Senior.

346
00:23:34,090 --> 00:23:35,150
Congratulations.

347
00:23:35,290 --> 00:23:36,180
From now on, you're a member

348
00:23:36,180 --> 00:23:37,380
of our Hot Music Club.

349
00:23:37,570 --> 00:23:38,170
Good!

350
00:23:38,690 --> 00:23:40,310
We found such a strong new member,

351
00:23:40,310 --> 00:23:41,200
so it's my treat.

352
00:23:41,200 --> 00:23:42,330
You're treating us?

353
00:23:42,920 --> 00:23:43,900
I,

354
00:23:43,980 --> 00:23:45,120
Xiao Yuchen,

355
00:23:44,900 --> 00:23:47,530
[Monument of Cultural
Exchange and Encounter]

356
00:23:45,120 --> 00:23:46,110
president of the Hot Music Club,

357
00:23:46,110 --> 00:23:48,100
am treating everyone today!

358
00:23:49,360 --> 00:23:50,120
Senior,

359
00:23:50,340 --> 00:23:51,830
I've got reward points here.

360
00:23:51,830 --> 00:23:52,680
I can use them to treat everyone.

361
00:23:52,680 --> 00:23:53,900
Reward pointss?

362
00:23:54,260 --> 00:23:55,230
And the caramel Earl Grey milk tea

363
00:23:55,230 --> 00:23:56,730
here

364
00:23:56,890 --> 00:23:57,380
is seriously amazing.

365
00:23:57,380 --> 00:23:58,180
One for me too.

366
00:23:59,950 --> 00:24:00,830
I'll get one as well.

367
00:24:00,830 --> 00:24:01,600
Same here.

368
00:24:02,930 --> 00:24:03,690
One more, thanks.

369
00:24:03,690 --> 00:24:04,410
Thanks, Senior.

370
00:24:04,410 --> 00:24:05,350
Then we'll leave it to you.

371
00:24:05,350 --> 00:24:07,750
Please deliver them to
the music club room.

372
00:24:08,800 --> 00:24:09,740
Senior He,

373
00:24:10,260 --> 00:24:11,920
everyone's ordered already.

374
00:24:12,190 --> 00:24:13,590
You're the only one left.

375
00:24:16,850 --> 00:24:18,020
Sometimes,

376
00:24:17,910 --> 00:24:19,950
[Monument of Cultural
Exchange and Encounter]

377
00:24:18,490 --> 00:24:20,390
when your heart beats faster,

378
00:24:20,620 --> 00:24:22,550
it's not because you were running,

379
00:24:22,580 --> 00:24:24,440
and it's not because it's too hot…

380
00:24:28,250 --> 00:24:29,770
It's because

381
00:24:29,930 --> 00:24:31,630
someone can understand

382
00:24:31,720 --> 00:24:33,780
your goodness without a single word.

383
00:24:34,620 --> 00:24:37,110
[Payment Method: Credit Card]

384
00:24:37,770 --> 00:24:38,470
Senior,

385
00:24:39,130 --> 00:24:40,510
why did you use your own card?

386
00:24:40,510 --> 00:24:42,300
You just joined the Hot Music Club.

387
00:24:42,300 --> 00:24:43,710
It's not your turn to treat us.

388
00:24:43,710 --> 00:24:44,800
But

389
00:24:45,080 --> 00:24:45,810
I have bonus points

390
00:24:45,810 --> 00:24:48,290
Just be a good kid and drink the beverage
I bought you.

391
00:24:48,290 --> 00:24:49,370
Jiayi.

392
00:24:54,370 --> 00:24:55,890
What do you mean by "Jiayi"?

393
00:24:55,890 --> 00:24:56,620
Didn't they

394
00:24:56,620 --> 00:24:58,110
always say "Jiayi"?

395
00:24:58,990 --> 00:24:59,630
I think from now on,

396
00:24:59,630 --> 00:25:00,790
your nickname

397
00:25:04,300 --> 00:25:05,640
should be Jiayi.

398
00:25:12,580 --> 00:25:13,810
At that moment,

399
00:25:14,230 --> 00:25:15,950
you want to get closer to him,

400
00:25:16,740 --> 00:25:19,050
but you don't know why.

401
00:25:33,160 --> 00:25:34,530
Sometimes,

402
00:25:34,530 --> 00:25:36,630
when your heart is beating that fast,

403
00:25:36,830 --> 00:25:38,490
you can't let it show too much.

404
00:25:44,830 --> 00:25:46,240
You're afraid

405
00:25:46,270 --> 00:25:49,690
your uncontrollable feelings might
bother the other person,

406
00:25:49,690 --> 00:25:52,850
so all you can do is try your hardest
to hide them.

407
00:25:53,210 --> 00:25:55,520
[Senior He]

408
00:25:53,320 --> 00:25:55,450
I added you to
the music club group chat,

409
00:25:55,450 --> 00:25:56,450
Jiayi.

410
00:25:56,880 --> 00:25:59,280
No matter how fast
our hearts were beating,

411
00:25:59,350 --> 00:26:01,120
that was our very first

412
00:26:01,420 --> 00:26:02,960
flutter of love.

413
00:28:26,380 --> 00:28:27,330
From now on,

414
00:28:26,890 --> 00:28:30,890
[Preview of the Next Episode]

415
00:28:27,330 --> 00:28:29,260
you're the guitarist for our band.

416
00:28:29,370 --> 00:28:31,420
I only know how to play simple melodies.

417
00:28:31,420 --> 00:28:33,210
If it's something more difficult…

418
00:28:33,210 --> 00:28:33,710
Come on.

419
00:28:34,410 --> 00:28:35,340
Let me teach you.

420
00:28:41,680 --> 00:28:42,780
Is he in your class?

421
00:28:42,900 --> 00:28:43,940
You mean Diaoqin?

422
00:28:44,080 --> 00:28:44,680
Yes.

423
00:28:44,820 --> 00:28:46,860
I'll help him study English later.

424
00:28:47,450 --> 00:28:48,890
Have you

425
00:28:48,890 --> 00:28:49,890
forgotten everything?
